- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses building and testing centralities to assess the importance of layers in multilayer stream graphs, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing large-scale datasets of interactions involving individuals, which is a common topic in computational social science. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses a new model for representing data and building centralities to analyze it, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses building and testing centralities, which is a common topic in machine learning.
